During a press briefing, Principal Deputy Press Secretary Eric Schultz discussed various topics including the EgyptAir crash, joint airstrikes with Russia in Syria, the President's upcoming trip to Vietnam, the Zika funding bill, and the rescue of Nigerian schoolgirls. Schultz also mentioned that President Obama will visit Hiroshima and lay a wreath at the Peace Memorial, but will not apologize for the atomic bombings in World War II.